@@TJvChooseIconDlg.Execute
Description:
Call this method to display the dialog. The function return true if the user has choosed an icon, and false if he has canceled the dialog. FileName and IconIndex specify the icon chossed by the user.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvChooseIconDlg.FileName
Description:
This property is the FileName containing the icon. It can be either an executable or a library. if this property is an empty string, the dialog assume it's the shell32 library. This property is modified when you call the execute method.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvChooseIconDlg.IconIndex
Description:
This property is the index of the icon in the executable or library. This property is modified when you call the execute method.

